reviews.text: Beautiful location and good food. Great place to hang out with friends and colleagues

Had drinks here and enjoyed sitting outside having a few beers. Staff were friendly. Some confusion over the way they prepare drinks to common convention (got black sambuca instead of baileys as part of a shot) but after a quick conversation, this was corrected.

Given that Enoteca had been renovated. Yet thing is very disappointed. Nothing is appealing at all. First, the food is tasteless. Secondly, service is slow. Thirdly, food choices are limited. result.name: Enoteca Quarry Bay

reviews.text: The Quarry Bay location is good for large groups. Great after work watering hole,  though I do miss some drinks that were taken off the menu after the renovation. La Pernacia was my favorite drink!
Our favourite after work haunt for a drink. Friendly, cheerful staff as well as good food 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
Always great, I always visit when in Hong Kong. Great staff and friendly service. Great selection of quality wines by the glass. Food is very good.

Enoteca is a fantastic place to get high quality tapas. They have a menu of at least 20 different delicious options, with photos to help you decide. Among my favourites are the baked Camembert, mushroom risotto balls, per peri chicken and the meatballs.

They also have a selection of beers on draught, including HK Yau, a collaboration between local brewers and Brooklyn Brewery. In all the times I've been, I've not had a single dish I haven't enjoyed. 

Definitely a great spot for a romantic dinner, a working lunch or a family style tapas session.
Good ambience, good food n service. A bit pricey but maybe worth it for overall experience
